name: Monty Python's Flying Circus
overview: A British sketch comedy series with the shows being composed of surreality, risqué or innuendo-laden humour, sight gags and observational sketches without punchlines.
tagline: And now for something completely different...

episodes.name: Whither Canada?
episodes.overview: Featuring 'It's Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart', an Italian lesson, Whizzo Butter, 'It's the Arts', Arthur 'Two-Sheds' Jackson, a cycling race, and The Funniest Joke in the World.

episodes.name: Sex and Violence
episodes.overview: Featuring some flying sheep, a man with three buttocks, a man with two noses, musical mice, a marriage guidance counsellor, a working-class playwright and The Wrestling Epilogue.

episodes.name: How to Recognise Different Types of Trees from Quite a Long Way Away
episodes.overview: Featuring a court scene, the larch, Bicycle Repair Man, children's stories, a restaurant sketch, some seduced milkmen, an interview with some children and a stolen newsreader.

episodes.name: Owl Stretching Time
episodes.overview: Featuring fresh fruit as self-defence, some folk-singing, an art gallery sketch and Lemming of the BDA. An Edwardian man struggles to undress on the beach.

episodes.name: Man's Crisis of Identity in the Latter Half of the 20th Century
episodes.overview: Featuring Confuse-a-Cat, discussion programme A Duck, a Cat and a Lizard, the arrest of a newsreader, an erotic film, a silly job interview and a burglar/encyclopaedia salesman.

episodes.name: It's the Arts
episodes.overview: Featuring a gang of legal burglars, the Whizzo Quality Assortment, a Scottish wedding and a day in the life of a city stockbroker. Some film moguls try to impress their boss.

episodes.name: Oh, You're No Fun Anymore
episodes.overview: Featuring camel-spotting, an embezzler at a board-meeting and a science fiction tale about a Scotsman and a tennis-playing blancmange.

episodes.name: Full Frontal Nudity
episodes.overview: Featuring an art critic, some hermits, Hell's Grannies and the dead parrot sketch. Some newlyweds attempt to buy a bed and the mafia offer protecting to the army.

episodes.name: The Ant, An Introduction
episodes.overview: Featuring Ken Buddha, a man with a tape-recorder up his nose and a hairdresser who always wanted to be a lumberjack.

episodes.name: Untitled
episodes.overview: Featuring a bank robber in a lingerie shop, It's A Tree (with Arthur Tree), a vocational guidance counsellor, Ron Obvious and a gorilla librarian.

episodes.name: The Royal Philharmonic Orchestra Goes to the Bathroom
episodes.overview: The Royal Philharmonic Orchestra goes to the bathroom, a footballer is interviewed and Batley Townswomen's Guild re-enact the invasion of Pearl Harbour.

episodes.name: The Naked Ant
episodes.overview: Featuring the North Minehead by-election, the Upper Class Twit of the Year competition, Ken Shabby and a Party Political Broadcast on behalf of the Wood Party.

episodes.overview: Featuring some historical impersonations, a cinema usherette with a dead seabird, restaurant abuse and Probe Around On Crime.

episodes.name: The Spanish Inquisition

episodes.name: Déjà Vu
